47:     public static final String BOOTSTRAP_SERVERS_DOC = "A list of host/port pairs used to establish the initial connection to the Kafka cluster. "
48:                                                         + "Clients use this list to bootstrap and discover the full set of Kafka brokers. "
49:                                                         + "While the order of servers in the list does not matter, we recommend including more than one server to ensure resilience if any servers are down. "
50:                                                         + "This list does not need to contain the entire set of brokers, as Kafka clients automatically manage and update connections to the cluster efficiently. "
51:                                                         + "This list must be in the form <code>host1:port1,host2:port2,...</code>.";
52:     public static final String CLIENT_DNS_LOOKUP_CONFIG = "client.dns.lookup";
53:     public static final String CLIENT_DNS_LOOKUP_DOC = "Controls how the client uses DNS lookups. "
54:                                                        + "If set to <code>use_all_dns_ips</code>, connect to each returned IP "
55:                                                        + "address in sequence until a successful connection is established. "
56:                                                        + "After a disconnection, the next IP is used. Once all IPs have been "
57:                                                        + "used once, the client resolves the IP(s) from the hostname again "
58:                                                        + "(both the JVM and the OS cache DNS name lookups, however). "
59:                                                        + "If set to <code>resolve_canonical_bootstrap_servers_only</code>, "
60:                                                        + "resolve each bootstrap address into a list of canonical names. After "
61:                                                        + "the bootstrap phase, this behaves the same as <code>use_all_dns_ips</code>.";
